               <!-- Comments and Corrections -->
               <noteGrp type="scholarComments">
                  <note resp="corr.">Attribution The work translated by Weir in JRAS 1901, pp. 809-825, (published in London 1976 as Whose Knoweth Himself…) is actually, as OY thought, R. fî l ahadiyya (RG. 13) and not K. al-alif. Mss. Veliyuddin 51, pp 19a-26b. Inspection by JC/SH confirms that it was copied in 762H from an original in the Shaykh’s hand, but fails to reveal any mention of Jerusalem or the date 601H on this particular work. Shehit Ali 2813, 35a- 41a. Inspection by JC/SH reveals that this was written by Ayy¬b b. Badr in 621H in Damascus and read in front of Ibn ‘Arab∆.</note>
                  <note resp="additions_0">Publications K. al-alif , Beirut, 1997 (in Rasa⁄il Ibn ‘Arabi) K. al-Alif wa huwa kitåb al-aπadiyya, Cairo, 1996 Corr. L'ouvrage traduit par Weir (trad. Rédigée à Londres en 1976) est bien, comme O. Y. le supposait, la R. fî l ahadiyya (RG. 13) et non le K. al-alif. (MC) Re: RG. 26. K. al-Alif Carulla 2111, 26a-31b Shehit Ali 2813, 35-41 Listeners: the qadi Mu'inuddin (?) Abu Ishaq Ibrahim, son of the qadi Majduddin 'Umar, son of the qadi 'Abd al-'Aziz al-Qurashi; also, companion and friend of Shaykh, Abu Ishaq Ibrahim b. Ahmad al-Qurtubi (r.a.) Hudai 517, 10b-13a Written by Hudayi in 999H From SH</note>
                  <note resp="msAdd.">Corr.</note>
                  <note resp="JC">
                     <p/>
                     <p/>
                  </note>
                  <note resp="SH">
                     <p/>
                     <p/>
                  </note>
                  <note resp="AP">
