               <!-- Comments and Corrections -->
               <noteGrp type="scholarComments">
                  <note resp="corr.">The commentary attributed to Abd al-Karîm Jîlî is most probably not by him; on the subject, see the thesis of R. Atlagh, Contribution à l’étude de la pensée mystique d’Ibn Arabî et son école à travers l’œuvre de Abd al-Karî Jîlî, submitted at l’E.P.H.E., Paris, Décembre 2000.</note>
                  <note resp="additions_0">Publications Cairo 1986 Cairo n.d. Tehran, 1416H (in Raså⁄il Ibn ¡Arab∆) Beirut 1997 (in Raså¡il Ibn ¡Arab∆). Trans lations Into Spanish (abridged) by Asin Palacios, El Islam cristianizado, Madrid, 1931, pp. 433- 449. Into English by Terri Harris, Journey to the Lord of Power, New York, 1981. Corr. Le commentaire attribué à Abd al-Karîm Jîlî n'est certainement pas de lui ; voir à ce sujet le thèse de R. Atlagh, Contribution à l'étude de la pensée mystique d'Ibn Arabî et son école à travers l'˛uvre de Abd al-Karî Jîlî, soutenue à l'E.P.H.E., Paris, Décembre 2000. (MC) title: R. al-Anwar Veliyuddin 1686, 21b-26b According to OY read before SQ in 667. No actual date on the copy, but later in book same scribe notes that he copied the Mahasin al-majalis of Abu'l-'Abbas Ibn al-'Arif in Sha'ban 667H, bi-manzili mawlana wa-shaykhina wa-imamina wa-quda'ina ila-llah subhanahu. Probable that this is SQ but no definitive evidence. He also copied work by Sa'd al-din Hamuya, referring to him as deceased and as sayyidina, and then quoting comment by SQ on the work. Milli Yz A 571, 189b-196a Dated 668H in Konya Ayasofya 2063 Dated 703H in Damascus, copied from an original in the hand of IA Shehit Ali 1341, 70a-75b Dated 724H in Damascus, but no evidence of having been copied from an original (as OY suggests) Carulla 986 OY says this ms was written during lifetime of IA, but there is no evidence to suggest anything like this - the format and style on the contrary suggest a later date. Carulla 2111 Dated 915H in Damascus, no evidence of having been copied from an original (as OY suggests) Shehit Ali 2717, 26b-32b Dated 977H in Mecca, complete Hudayi 517 Dated 999H in Hudayi's hand Manisa 2964, 61-67a Dated 1083H in Edirne title: K. Asrar al-khalwa Yusuf Aga 7838, 44a-53b, (classified by OY as RG 255) dated 651H, checked with original, from SQ's library Sama on 44a in SQ’s hand: This treatise was read in the house of M. Ibn Sawdakin on 1st Ramadan 651H by Muhamad b. Ishaq. b. Muhammad (=SQ) Marginal corrections throughout. 53b in SQ’s hand: checked and corrected against the shaykh’s own copy. Manisa 2989, 121a-132b, n.d. From SH</note>
                  <note resp="msAdd.">Veliyuddin 1826, 5-11b, eao, carries a sema⁄ dated 621H</note>
