                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">Verified by at least five historic mss. The holograph Yusuf Aga 4868 was written in 615H in Malatya, and Carullah 2111 is copied from an original which was read before IA. According to OY, it was written 601H in Jerusalem on the basis of a note on Veliyuddin 51, but our investigation shows that no place or date is given. (See Jane Clark and Denis McAuley Some Notes on the Manuscript Veliyyudin 51, JMIAS 40, 2006.)</note>
