               <note type="compositionNote"/>
               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">A list by Ibn ʿArabi himself of his works, consisting of 248 different titles. It was written before 627H (see Hamidiye 188), therefore does not include later works. Critical edition by Bakri Aladdin 2020</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY lists 13 mss., of which three can be considered historic. The best is Yusuf Aga 7838, written by SQ probably during lifetime of IA, although it may be incomplete. Hamidiye 188 is a copy of this original with added works dated 627H and 628H, with a samāʿ given by IA. The same is true of Majāmiʿ 340.</note>
