               <!-- Editions, Translations, and Relevant Publications -->
               <noteGrp type="publications">
                  <note type="editions">Beirut edition edited by Abu ʿAlā ʿAfīfī (Beirut, nd) is based upon several mss. but did not use the Ṣādr al-dīn al-Qūnawī autograph (Evkaf Musezi 1933). A new critical edition using the Qūnawī autograph, plus a translation into Urdu, by the Ibn ʿArabī Foundation (Rawalpindi, Pakistan). Ed. Abrār Aḥmad Shāhī. Critical edition by ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz al-Manṣūb (with Abrār Aḥmad Shāhī) (Cairo 2016) based on mss. from the MIAS archive. A critical edition alongside Naqsh al-Fuṣūṣ, with complete references to Qurʾān and ḥadith by Dr Saiyad Nizamuddin al-Husayni (Cairo, date unknown). Critical edition by Mahmud Kiliç and Abdurrahim Alkiṣ (Istanbul 2016), fully vowelled based upon al-Kashānī’s commentary plus a facsmile of the oldest ms, Evkaf Muzesi 1933, written by Ṣadr al-dīn al-Qūnawi.</note>
                  <note type="translations">English Partial translation (12 chapters only) by Angela Culme-Seymour, based upon Burckhardt’s French translation: The Wisdom of the Prophets, Glos, 1975. Full translation by ʿAisha ʿAbd al-Rahman at-Tarjumana: The Seals of Wisdom, Norwich, 1980. Full translation by R W J Austin: The Bezels of Wisdom, New York, 1981. Full rendering alongside the commentary by ʿAbd Allah Bosnawī by Bulent Rauf: Fuṣūṣ al-ḥikam, Vols 1-4, Oxford, 1981-6: Second Edition, 1994. Full translation by Caner K Dagli: The Ringstones of Wisdom, Chicago, 2004. Full translation by Binyamin Abrahmov, Ibn al-ʿArabi’s Fusus al-hikam, London, 2015. French Partial translation (12 chapters only) by Titus Burckhardt: La Sagesse des Prophètes, Paris, 1974. Full translation by Charles-André Gilis: Le Livre des Chatons des Sagesse, Vols 1 &amp; 2, Paris, 1998. Full translation by Paul Ballanfat: Les Chatons des sagesses et les demeures des paroles (Combes, 2020) Italian Italian translation by Titus Burckhardt, La sapienza dei Profeti, Roma, 1987 (partial translation: only 12 chapters)</note>
                  <note type="translationsEur">German Full translation by Hans Kofler:Fuṣūṣ al-Ḥikam, Graz (Austria), 1970. Partial translation based upon Burkhardt: Die Weisheit der propheten, Zurich, 2001. Partial translation by Alma Geise: Ibn ʿArabī: Urwolke und Welt, Munich 2002. Spanish Full translation by Abderramán Mohamed Maanán: Los Engarces de la sabiduría, Madrid, 1994. Full translation by Andrés Guijarro: Los engarces de las sabidurías, Madrid, 2009. Italian Partial translation by Giorgio Jannaccone; Titus Burckhardt: La sapienza dei profeti , Rome, 1987. Serbo-Croat Full translation by Resid Hafizovic: Dragulji Poslanicke Mudrosti Fuṣūs al-Ḥikam, Zenica, 1995.</note>
