               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">This work is also known by various names, e.g. Ḥizb al-ʿārif billāh, often occurring with copies of the Awrād (RG 64). All extant copies are post-1000H. There is nothing to substantiate authenticity, and Stephen Hirtenstein, who has examined the mss., all of which are attributed to IA, believes that the internal evidence is fair. To check: Escurial, reference 132 6/417</note>
