               <note type="compositionNote"/>
               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">The symbolism of the personal pronoun ‘He’ (huwā), represented, in the order of the alphabet, by the last letter, yāʾ.</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY cites 26 mss., of which three are historic. The best are Veliyuddin 51, 762H(c), copied from an original in the hand of IA, and Yusuf Ağa 7838 which is undated, but from SQ’s library so presumed before 673H. According to OY, it was written 601H in Jerusalem on the basis of a note on Veliyuddin 51, but our investigation shows that he has confused the place of copying with the place of writing and in fact, no place or date is given. (See Jane Clark and Denis McAuley Some Notes on the Manuscript Veliyyudin 51, JMIAS 40, 2006.)</note>
