                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY cites four mss., all of them late. According to him, the preface is identical to ʿUqlat al-mustawfiz (RG802) but the end differs – our preliminary inspection indicates that the beginning is a variant, and it goes up to end of chapter on falak al-kawākib, with an extra piece at the end. Similar in content to Chapter 7 in FM. Needs some further research to determine whether this is really an independent work.</note>
