               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">Commentary upon the verses of the Qurʾān, conceived as a companion volume to al-Tanazzulāt al-Mawṣiliyya (RG 762). Written for IA’s companion, Badr al-Ḥabashī.</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY cites 10 mss., verified by two historic mss., Veliyuddin 51 (c.762H, taken from original in the hand of IA dated 601H) and Yusuf Ağa 7838. According to OY, written 602H in Jerusalem on the basis of a note on Veliyuddin 51, but our investigation shows that he has confused the place of copying with the place of writing and in fact, no place is given. The date given is Ramadan 601H, when it is known that IA was in Malatya. (See Jane Clark and Denis McAuley Some Notes on the Manuscript Veliyyudin 51, JMIAS 40, 2006.)</note>
