               <placeName type="fmPlace"/>
               <note type="placeNote">Note on Place of Composition</note>
               <note type="compositionNote">A letter was written by IA for Abū l-Fawāris Ṣakhr b. Sinān (Vel.51/48a)</note>
               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">A poetical work on the perfect human being (al-insān al-kāmil), the supreme intellect, the guarded tablet, the materia prima, and the universal body. One of IA’s earlier Maghribi works. See Angela Jaffray’s introduction and translation, The Universal Tree and the Four Birds (Oxford, 2005).</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY cites 21 mss., of which three are historic mss. The best are Shehit Ali 2813 (621H, written by Ayyūb b. Badr in the presence of IA) and Veliyuddin 51 (c. 762H, copied from al-Ḥabashī’s original).</note>
