               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">On retreat in general, but mentioning some particular kinds of retreat at end, e.g. the hoopoe retreat. Written for Abū al-ʿAbbās Aḥmad b. ʿAlī b. Maymūn b. Ab al-Tawzarī (see Chapter 69 of FM (1:91)).</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">A much copied work under various titles, verified by three historic mss. The earliest is either Koprulu 766 (pre-638?) or Veliyuddin 1686 (c.667). Sometimes confused with R. al-Anwār (RG 33). Mentioned in both FM and Maqām al-qurba.</note>
