               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">A late work, it gives a detailed list of ‘investitures’ through which the Shaykh received initiation into the Path, including one by the hidden guide, al-Khiḍr.</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY lists 19 mss., of which one can be considered historic: Esad Ef. 1507 (999H, copied from an original dated 633H in IA’s handwriting and corrected by him). Many mss. are incomplete. Veliyuddin 51 contains only the 599H khirqa, but it is also copied from an original in the hand of IA. Further mss: Bankipore ms 955/2 (778H?)</note>
