               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Migration Notes -->
               <note type="migrationNote">Dating Denis and Jane: “Osman Yahia maintains that the work was composed in Mosul in 601, and he gives as his source not Veliyuddin 51 but a reference in Brockelmann, who lists other manuscripts, outside Turkey, which we have not yet inspected.” This could make sense given qas_ilah was composed in Mosul on this date in the same collection...</note>
               <!-- Editions, Translations, and Relevant Publications -->
               <noteGrp type="publications">
                  <note type="editions"/>
                  <note type="translations">English translation by Tosun Bayrak al-Jerrahi: ‘What the Student Needs: Ibn ʿArabī’s Ma la budda minhu lil-murid’ in JMIAS 5, 1986, pp. 28-55. English Translation by Tosun Bayrak and Rabia Terri Harris: What the Seeker Needs, USA, 1993 English translation by Shaykh Tosun Bayrak: Divine Governance of the Human Kingdom, plus ‘What the seeker needs’ and ‘Treatise on Unity’, Louisville, 1997. English translation by James Morris in his paper From ethics and devotion to spiritual realisation : Ibn ‘Arabî on what is indispensable for the spiritual seeker, Kuala Lumpur : Centre for Civilisational Dialogue, University of Malaysia, 2007, 32 p. Italian translation by Placido Fontanesi, Il libro di ciò che è essenziale riguardo a quanto è indispensabile per l’aspirante, Rivista di studi tradizionali, 1982, pp. 7-22</note>
                  <note type="translationsEur">Spanish translation by Mohammed Amrani &amp; Alfonso González: Guía Espiritual, Murcia, 1990 Spanish translation by Tosun Bayrak al-Jerrahi al-Halveti, Afife Traverso and Emilio Alzueta: El divino gobierno del reino humano, Lo que necesita el buscador tratador sobre el uno y único, Granada, 2004.</note>
