               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">A series of letters from the author to different people, some containing poems.</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY lists four mss., none of which are definitively historic. Internal evidence for attribution (e.g. mention of Seville, al-Muḥāsibī, al-Shakkāz in Granada, Ibn Saydabūn) is compelling, however. There is a lot of variation in the number of letters, with Fatih 5322 giving 43 in total, Carullah 986 22 and Carullah 2080 only 13. Further mss identified by JC: Uppsala 162/15 (ff.77b-82a)</note>
