               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">A work on Islamic law (fiqh). In Fihris muʾallafāt al-shaykh al-akbar (RG142), IA says that he composed this work in Mecca in three parts: the first on ritual purity, the second and third on the prayer itself. There is just one extant copy, which is the second part of the work.</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">Verified by one historic ms., Yusuf Ağa 4986, an autograph dated 600H which was part of SQ’s library. Original ms. was stolen, so we only have a digital copy of a photocopy. According to information in Konya, the book was gifted to SQ’s mother as a wedding gift by IA.</note>
