            <bibl xml:id="mukh_dur">
               <idno type="RG">496</idno>
               <idno type="Alt_RG">105</idno>
               <idno type="RECORDID">597</idno>
               <idno type="Normalized">mukh_dur</idno>
               <!-- Titles -->
               <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="uniform">K. Mukhtaṣar al-Durra al-fākhira</title>
               <title xml:lang="ara" type="uniform-ara">كتاب مختصر الدرة الفاخرة</title>
               <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="full"/>
               <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="variant"/>
               <title xml:lang="eng" type="translationEng"/>
               <note type="titleNote">Note on Title</note>
               <!-- Textual Identifiers -->
               <incipit type="hamdala" xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">al-ḥamdu lillāh rabb al-ʿālamīn wa-l-ʿāqaba li-l-muttaqīn...</incipit>
               <incipit type="hamdala-ara" xml:lang="ara">Arabic Script Incipit</incipit>
               <incipit type="muqadimma" xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">First Line of Intro (after ḥamdala )</incipit>
               <incipit type="muqadimma" xml:lang="ara">First Line of Intro (Arabic script)</incipit>
               <incipit type="khutba" xml:lang="ara">Complete Khuṭba</incipit>
               <explicit xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Closing Words of Text (exclusive of any rubric or colophon which might follow it).</explicit>
               <explicit type="muqadimma" xml:lang="ara">Closing Words of Text (Arabic script)</explicit>
               <note type="textualIdentifiersNote">Note on Textual Identifiers</note>
               <!-- Authorship and Editorial Roles -->
               <author cert="medium" key="IA">Ibn al-ʿArabī</author>
               <editor role="role" key="key">Other Roles</editor>
               <persName role="att" key="IA">Ibn al-ʿArabī</persName>
               <note type="authenticityNote">Note on Authenticity</note>
               <!-- Composition History -->
               <date type="fmDate" calendar="Hijri-qamari"/>
               <date type="fmEarliestMS" calendar="Hijri-qamari"/>
               <date when="1111" cert="high" calendar="Hijri-qamari">Date of Composition</date>
               <date from="1111" to="1111" cert="medium" calendar="Hijri-qamari">Period of Composition</date>
               <date notBefore="1111"
                     notAfter="1111"
                     cert="low"
                     calendar="Hijri-qamari"
                     evidence="conjecture">Terminus post quem and terminus ante quem</date>
               <note type="dateNote">Note on Date of Composition</note>
               <placeName type="fmPlace"/>
               <note type="placeNote">Note on Place of Composition</note>
               <note type="compositionNote"/>
               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">Autobiographical sketches of IA’s masters in al-Andalus, a companion volume to his Rūḥ al-quds (RG 639). This work was written in Andalusia, and therefore there are no extant manuscripts of the original work. However, Ibn ʿArabī rewrote a version of the text later for a friend in Damascus, and this is the text, entitled K. Mukhtaṣar al-Durra al-fākhira, that we now have. Abrar Ahmad adds: Shaykh Ibn Arabi says in the first paragraph of this Mukhtaṣar al-Durra al-Fākhira: سألني بعض من يكرم علي من إخواني بمحروسة دمشق أن أوقفه على كتاب أودعته ذكر بعض من لقيته فانتفعت به في طريق الأخرة فلم يكن عندي حاضرا عند سواله فإني تركته بالمغرب فقيدت له هذا المختصر في ذكر بعض المشيخة؟ من أهل الله المتمكنين في طريق أهل التحقيق من الصالحين العارفين رضي الله عنهم جميعهم مستعينًا بالله تعالى ولم أذكر فيه إلا من لقيته ورأيته وصحبته من رجال ونساء وكبير في السن وصغير على قدر ما تذكرت منهم في هذا الوقت. وذكرت على كل واحد منهم حكاية رأيتها منه من كلام حكمة أو خرق عادة أو موعظة و تركت منهم كثيرا أضعاف ما ذكرت. (مختصر الدرة الفاخرة - الصفحة الأولي للمخطوط)</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">There are only two extant mss.: one, Esad Ef. 1777, is listed by OY as Al-durrat al-fākhira (RG 105) and is late (1006H); the other OY lists as RG 496, K. Mukhtaṣar al-durrat al-fākhira in Veliyuddin 1800. OY lists Esad Efendi under both classifications, and Veliyuddin 1800/186-201B, under RG 496 only. We would suggest that they should both be under RG 496. The Veliyuddin ms. is early (715H) and presumably the source for Esad Ef. The main factor in considering this a verified work is the correlation with the well-verified work Rūḥ al-quds (RG 639) and the fact that it relates many of the same incidents.</note>
