               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">A series of dhikrs (rememorations of God) and their effects for those who are brought close to the divine presence (the muqarribūn) .</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY lists five mss., none of which can be considered definitive or historic. The British Library OR 9632, however, which OY did not see, was written during Ibn ʿArabī’s lifetime by one of his known students, and is definitive in attributing it to him. OY says that the author quotes an event in 631H which would support the possibility of attribution. In addition, a work of this title is listed in both the lists which IA made of his own works, Fihris muʾallafāt al-shaykh al-akbar (RG142) and Ijāza li-l-malik al-Muẓaffar (RG 269).</note>
