               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">The nuqabāʾ (sing. naqīb) are a category of 300 saints in the spiritual hierarchy. Defined by IA in his list of Sufi terminology (Iṣṭilāḥāt al-Ṣuƒiyya, RG 315) as those who uncover the hidden aspects of the self (nafs).</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY lists nine mss. of which four can be considered historic. The best are Veliyuddin 51 (c.762H, copied from an original in the hand of IA) and Manisa 1183 (655H, written by a direct disciple of IA’s). Manisa ms gives the names of 12 nuqabāʾ from the time of the Prophet, but these vary in other mss.</note>
