               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY lists 33 mss., of which at least three can be considered historic. The best is Shehit Ali 2813 (621H in Damascus, written by Ayyūb b. Badr and checked by IA) and Berlin 2921 (637H). Other good copies, Murad Bukhari 207 and Veliyuddin 1826, were taken from Ayyūb b. Badr’s copy.</note>
