               <!-- Migration Notes -->
               <note type="migrationNote"/>
               <!-- Editions, Translations, and Relevant Publications -->
               <noteGrp type="publications">
                  <note type="editions">An edition established by H S Nyberg in Kleinere Schriften des Ibn al-ʿArabî, (Leiden, 1919). A recent critical edition, plus an Urdu translation, published by The Ibn ʿArabī Foundation (Rawalpindi, Pakistan, 2014), edited by Abrār Aḥmad Shāhī. This is based upon the best early manuscripts as found in the MIAS archive, including Yusuf Ağa 4859 and Koprulu 713, but not the autograph Leiden Or 86, which had not yet been identified when the text was edited.</note>
                  <note type="translations">English translation by Shaykh Tosun Bayrak: Divine Governance of the Human Kingdom, plus ‘What the seeker needs’ and ‘Treatise on Unity’, Louisville, 1997.</note>
                  <note type="translationsEur">Spanish translation by Tosun Bayrak al-Jerrahi al-Halveti, Afife Traverso and Emilio Alzueta: El divino gobierno del reino humano, Lo que necesita el buscador tratador sobre el uno y único, Granada, 2004.</note>
                  <note type="additions_1"/>
                  <note type="additions_2">A very interpretative translation exists by Tosun Bayrak called ‘Divine Governance of the Human Kingdom’</note>
                  <note type="additions_3">Asin Palacios, in El. Isl, Crist, pp352-370</note>
               </noteGrp>
