               <note type="stemmatics">There is only one ms. listed in OY (he also erroneously classifies it under RG 684). We have found another ms., Halet 809, which is identical (NB: OY also lists this as RG 731). The Shehit Ali text mentions “our shaykh Abū Madyan saying that he never saw a thing except that there was the letter bāʾ over it”, which makes this a bona fide ms.</note>
