               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">Strophic poem consisting of 5-line stanzas – a poetic expansion of verses by Abū Madyan. See translation and study by Gerald Elmore: ‘Ibn al-ʿArabī’s ‘Cinquain’ (Takhmīs) on a poem by Abū Madyan’ in Arabica Vol. 46, 1998, pp. 63-96.</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">Only three mss. listed by OY. We have looked at two of them, both late copies with no historical evidence to support attribution to IA. The content, however, strongly favours the attribution. See translation and study by Gerald Elmore in Arabica Vol. 46, 1998, pp. 63-96. Further work needed.</note>
