               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">Work composed in Mosul in 601H, on the esoteric significance of ablution and prayers, describing how each phase of everyday ritual is imbued with meaning. Consists of 55 chapters.</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">OY lists 31 mss., and it is verified by at least nine historic mss. The best is a holograph, Murad Bukhari 162 (with a samāʿ dated 620H and a note verifying that it was written by IA), Murad Molla 1257 (621H, written by Ayyūb b. Badr) and Yusuf Ağa 4861 (written by SQ).</note>
