               <!-- Migration Notes -->
               <note type="migrationNote">Related work: dhakhair (116) - commentary</note>
               <!-- Editions, Translations, and Relevant Publications -->
               <noteGrp type="publications">
                  <note type="editions">Critical Edition published by R A Nicholson and published alongside his English translation The Tarjumān al-ashwāq (London, 1911). However, the manuscripts he used were all late and had no special provenance.</note>
                  <note type="translations">Full English translation of the poems, but not the commentary, by R A Nicholson: The Tarjumān al-ashwāq, London, 1911. Full English translation by Michael Sells: The Translator of Desires, Princeton, 2021. Partial English translation by Michael Sells: Stations of Desire, Jerusalem, 2000. Translation of the Preface by Jane Clark available on http://www.ibnarabisociety.org/articlespdf/preface-tarjuman-al-ashwaq.pdf French translation of poems and commentary by Maurice Gloton, L’interprète des désirs, Paris, 1996. Partial French translation by Mahmoud Sami-Ali: Le chant de l'ardent désir, Arles 2006. Italian translation by Roberto Rossi Testa, L’interprete delle passioni, Milano, 2008</note>
                  <note type="translationsEur">Spanish translation by Carlos Varona Narvión: El intérprete de los deseos, Murcia, 2002. Partial German translation by Alma Geise: Ibn ʿArabī: Urwolke und Welt, Munich 2002.</note>
                  <note type="additions_1"/>
                  <note type="additions_2"/>
                  <note type="additions_3">Nicholson, London, 1911</note>
               </noteGrp>
