               <!-- Contents -->
               <noteGrp type="workDesc">
                  <note type="description">The perfect human being (al-insān al-kāmil) and the multiple degrees of Being from the most elevated orders of the Archangels to inorganic nature (OY).</note>
                  <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
                  <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
               </noteGrp>
               <!-- Stemmatics -->
               <note type="stemmatics">An often copied work, verified by three historic mss. The best is Yusuf Ağa 4690 (undated and incomplete, but in IA’s handwriting); also Shehit Ali 1341 (725H, said to have been taken from an original, which may have been by IA) and Ayasofya 4875 (dated 753H).</note>
               <!-- Related Works -->
               <relatedItem type="type" target="#work_id"/>
               <note type="relationsNote">Note on Related Works</note>
               <!-- References to This Work in Other Works -->
               <noteGrp type="references2ThisWork">
